latestPosts.caption:
Posted @withregram • @toraniofficial My first memory of Mona Singh, like many others, was watching her in the iconic Jassi Jaisi Koi Nahin—a character that left an indelible mark on Indian television. Since then, she has evolved into a formidable actor, finding her own voice and space in the industry. Yet, despite over two decades in the spotlight, Mona remains soft-spoken, deeply warm, and profoundly affectionate—qualities rarely associated with those who have spent so long in the craft.

Working with her on Juloos was a dream, not just because of her artistry but because of what she represents. She is an actor who allows herself to be molded, who embraces transformation, and who carries a presence that feels like home—familiar, comforting, yet undeniably powerful. At Torani, we have always sought artists who bridge the distance between fashion and reality, making it something tangible, lived, and felt. Mona embodies that spirit, and I am deeply grateful for her presence in this journey.

Featuring @monajsingh
